x^p-x
p
\mathbb Z_p
p
x^p-x=x(x-1)\cdots(x-p+1)
\rm mod\ p\!:\,\ f(x)=x^p\!-x\:\Rightarrow\:f(x\!+\!1) = \color{#C00}{(x\!+\!1)^p}\!-x\!-\!1 \,\equiv\, \color{#C00}{x^p\!+1^p}\!-x\!-\!1 \,\equiv\, x^p\! - x = f(x)
\rm\ f(x\!+\!1)\equiv f(x)\ 
\rm\ f(p\!-\!1)\equiv f(p\!-\!2)\equiv \cdots \equiv f(1)\equiv f(0)\equiv 0.
